article.headline: Houston rallies from 12 down in first half
article.linkText: Houston downs TCU to win Conference USA
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Chandi Jones scored 26 points and made four free
throws in the final 24 seconds to help Houston (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) win the
Conference USA regular-season championship with a 76-71 victory
Friday night over Texas Christian (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 13 AP).

Houston (24-3, 13-1) trailed 50-38 with 17:03 left, but the Lady
Cougars ended the game by outscoring TCU 38-21. The Lady Frogs
(22-5, 11-3) lost despite 21 points, 19 rebounds and seven blocks
by Sandora Irvin.

Houston took its first lead with 9:07 remaining when Nicole
Oliver connected on two free throws.

The Cougars led by six points with 35 seconds remaining when
TCU's Kim Ortega hit a 3-pointer to cut the lead to 71-68. TCU had
a chance to tie, but Adrianne Ross threw up an air ball that Jones
rebounded.

Jones hit two free throws on the other end, and after Tiffany
Evans missed a 3-point attempt for TCU, Jones hit two more free
throws to seal the win.

Sancho Lyttle added 14 points and seven rebounds for Houston,
and Oliver scored 14 points. Ortega added 17 points for TCU.

TCU led by as many as 12 points in the first half and had a
43-34 edge at the break.
